<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-43-0289 </DOCNO><TEXT>Questions of offering medical aid to victims of combined nuclear weaponinjuries (radiation-thermal, radiation-mechanical, radiation-thermomechanical,thermomechanical) are discussed. During the early diagnosis the victimsare classified into four groups with regard to multiplicity and heterogeneityof disfunctions occuring in each victim with the evaluation of theirmutual forecasting effect on the outcomes. Pathology peculiaties in victimsof combined injuries, diagnostic difficulties are indicated; recommendationsconcerning medical aid organization are given.</TEXT></DOC>